      An abstract visual has as many motifs as it has viewers. Each person who looks at it must inevitably create their
own interpretation of what they see. Each of these individual interpretations is indeed as true and real as all the others.

The „metaverse“ created the possibility to implement already existing, 2 dimensional artworks (done with psd) into a 3 dimensional space, that you can simply walk through.

directly in the browser

just 1 click away

YGGDRASILL – the world-tree

go there now

The interconnectedness of everything, which plays such a central role in today's reality, is here captured with different, mostly technological textures and forms.

BUTTERFLIES IN SPACE

go there now

This is a virtual walk-through sculpture that serves a single purpose - to please the eyes and find yourself in another dimension for a moment.
 

screencanvas

What if your screen
was the canvas?

This is the idea of creating a digital painting that resides on a server and can be accessed from any device - just like a website.

It exists exclusively on the web and uses effects like parallax and animations to interact with the viewer in a way only a website can do.

OIL PAINT ON DIGITAL ARTWORK

Through very often repeated application of visual effects, digital shapes and structures are created, which are then arranged to create the digital basis for the image. After printing it is finished with color and various classical painting techniques.

The fascination of digital and analogue textures
